The paper discusses the design and implementation of a new full-text index for compressing and encrypting collections of genomic sequences, which is relevant to the fields of database management (cs.DB) and cryptography (cs.CR). The index is optimized for fast pattern-search queries, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of encryption models and software, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CC). Finally, the implementation of the index in C++ and the availability of the source code and performance data suggest a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
